mp7001MIBversion.name: mp7001MIBversion
mp7001MIBversion.description: Identifies the version of the MIB. The format of the version is x.yzT, where 'x' identifies the major revision number, 'y' identifies the minor revision number, 'z' identifies the typographical revision, and T identifies the test revision. Acceptable values for the individual revision components are as follows: x: 1 - 9 y: 0 - 9 z: 0 - 9 T: A - Z Upon formal release, no designation for the test revision will be present.

mp7001VersionEntry.name: mp7001VersionEntry
mp7001VersionEntry.description: An entry in the GDC Mp7001System Version Table.

mp7001VersionIndex.name: mp7001VersionIndex
mp7001VersionIndex.description: Integer value which uniquely identifies the MP7001 to which this entry is applicable. SCinstance is defined to be ssllddcc where: ss (byte value) - physical shelf slot location (01-32) ll (byte value) - line number (01-128) dd (byte value) - drop number (00-31) cc (byte value) - channel or interface number (always 00)

mp7001FirmwareRev.name: mp7001FirmwareRev
mp7001FirmwareRev.description: The version number of the firmware, to allow products to know which revision is installed. The released version number is sequenced from --, A-, ... AA, ... ZZ.

mp7001CardType.name: mp7001CardType
mp7001CardType.description: This variable is used to determine the type of card family installed ex. MP7001.

mp7001BootRev.name: mp7001BootRev
mp7001BootRev.description: The version number of the boot firmware, to allow products to know which revision is installed. The released version number is sequenced from --, A-, ... AA, ... ZZ.

mp7001MaintenanceTable.name: mp7001MaintenanceTable
mp7001MaintenanceTable.description: The table describes the maintenance objects for MP 7001.

mp7001MaintenanceEntry.name: mp7001MaintenanceEntry
mp7001MaintenanceEntry.description: An entry in the GDC 701 Maintenance Table.

mp7001MaintenanceLineIndex.name: mp7001MaintenanceLineIndex
mp7001MaintenanceLineIndex.description: Integer value which uniquely identifies the MP7001 to which this entry is applicable. SCinstance is defined to be ssllddcc where: ss (byte value) - physical shelf slot location (01-32) ll (byte value) - line number (01-128) dd (byte value) - drop number (00-31) cc (byte value) - channel or interface number (always 00)

mp7001SoftReset.name: mp7001SoftReset
mp7001SoftReset.description: Supports the action of soft resetting the unit. When this object is set to reset(2), then the unit performs a soft reset, whose meaning is specific to the type of unit being managed. The value of norm(1) will be returned when the reset is complete. The value of norm(1) can not be set by management.

mp7001SysUpTime.name: mp7001SysUpTime
mp7001SysUpTime.description: This variable is used to report the elapsed system tick time for conversion to real time at the controller and is not related to the sysUpTime referenced in MIB-II. Upon power-up of the unit, the elapsed time is cleared. The elapsed time counter rolls over upon reaching the maximum count.

mp7001DefaultInit.name: mp7001DefaultInit
mp7001DefaultInit.description: This is used to allow the NonVolatile Configuration to be set to a factory default state. When this value is set to factoryDefault(2) the unit will perform a reset to make the default configuration take affect. The value of normal(1) will be returned when the initialization is complete. The value of normal(1) can not be set by management.

mp7001ResetStats.name: mp7001ResetStats
mp7001ResetStats.description: Supports the action of soft resetting the mp7001ValidIntervals object. When this object is set to reset(2), then the unit will reset the mp7001ValidIntervals object to zero. The value of norm(1) can not be set by management.

mp7001LedStatus.name: mp7001LedStatus
mp7001LedStatus.description: Returns a bitwise snapshot of the front panel LED state. Octet 1 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - ON bit 5 - INSV bit 4 - RSP bit 3 - TMG bit 2 - future use bit 1 - future use bit 0 - future use Octet 2 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - future use bit 5 - NTWK AIS bit 4 - NTWK LCV bit 3 - NTWK LOS bit 2 - NTWK OOF bit 1 - ALM bit 0 - TM

mp7001T1CircuitName.name: mp7001T1CircuitName
mp7001T1CircuitName.description: Circuit name T1 is connected to.

mp7001SetRealTime.name: mp7001SetRealTime
mp7001SetRealTime.description: Number of seconds from midnight Dec 31, 1969.

mp7001AlarmStatus.name: mp7001AlarmStatus
mp7001AlarmStatus.description: Returns a bit-wise Status of alarms Octet 1 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - NTWK LOS bit 5 - NTWK LOF bit 4 - NWTK_AIS bit 3 - future use bit 2 - NTWK Received YELLOW bit 1 - NTWK Excessive Zeros - not supported bit 0 - NTWK Low Average Density - not supported Octet 2 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - NTWK BiPolar Violations bit 5 - NTWK CRC Errors bit 4 - NTWK Controlled Slips bit 3 - Unavailable Signal State bit 2 - Status Change bit 1 - Timing Loss bit 0 - Unit Failure Octet 3 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - future use bit 5 - future use bit 4 - future use bit 3 - future use bit 2 - future use bit 1 - future use bit 0 - future use Octet 4 bit 7 - not used bit 6 - ES bit 5 - BES bit 4 - SES bit 3 - UAS bit 2 - Unsolicited Test bit 1 - NVRAM checksum corrupted bit 0 - Power-up Alarm

mp7001SystemTimingGenStatus.name: mp7001SystemTimingGenStatus
mp7001SystemTimingGenStatus.description: Indicates if the units configured for primary or secondary system clock are actually supplying clock and if it is the 8hkz, 4mhz, or both.

mp7001StatLastInitialized.name: mp7001StatLastInitialized
mp7001StatLastInitialized.description: Number of seconds from midnight Dec 31, 1969 up until mp7001ValidIntervals was last initialized to zero

mp7001ValidIntervals.name: mp7001ValidIntervals
mp7001ValidIntervals.description: The number of previous intervals for which valid data was collected. The value will be 96 unless the interface was brought on-line within the last 24 hours, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals the since interface has been online.

mp7001ConfigIndex.name: mp7001ConfigIndex
mp7001ConfigIndex.description: Integer value which uniquely identifies the MP7001 to which this entry is applicable. SCinstance is defined to be ssllddcc where: ss (byte value) - physical shelf slot location (01-32) ll (byte value) - line number (01-128) dd (byte value) - drop number (00-31) cc (byte value) - channel or interface number (always 00)

mp7001NetworkInterfaceType.name: mp7001NetworkInterfaceType
mp7001NetworkInterfaceType.description: Sets the transmit range to DSX-1 short or DS-1 long

mp7001FallbackClockSource.name: mp7001FallbackClockSource
mp7001FallbackClockSource.description: Identifies the fallback transmit clock source.

mp7001Framing.name: mp7001Framing
mp7001Framing.description: Set the framing for the interface. Abbreviations are as follows: eSF - Extended Super Frame d4 - Super Frame

mp7001LineCoding.name: mp7001LineCoding
mp7001LineCoding.description: Sets the line coding for the interface.

mp7001LineBuildout.name: mp7001LineBuildout
mp7001LineBuildout.description: Sets the line build out for the interface 0, -7.5, -15 or -22.5dB

mp7001FDLMode.name: mp7001FDLMode
mp7001FDLMode.description: Sets the Facility Data Link Mode.

mp7001AISLoopdown.name: mp7001AISLoopdown
mp7001AISLoopdown.description: Sets AIS unloop time where 4 = inhibit, 5 thru 60 = number of seconds

mp7001SysTimingIndex.name: mp7001SysTimingIndex
mp7001SysTimingIndex.description: Integer value which uniquely identifies the MP7001 to which this entry is applicable. SCinstance is defined to be ssllddcc where: ss (byte value) - physical shelf slot location (01-32) ll (byte value) - line number (01-128) dd (byte value) - drop number (00-31) cc (byte value) - channel or interface number (always 00)

mp7001SysTimingGen.name: mp7001SysTimingGen
mp7001SysTimingGen.description: Selects if the unit provides system timing. none(1) - does not provide Timing Generator primary(2) - unit is primary Timing Generator for the shelf. secondary(3) - unit is secondary Timing Generator for the shelf. Only 1 unit in the shelf can the primary or secondary timing generator. All other must be none.

mp7001DCCConfigurationTable.name: mp7001DCCConfigurationTable
mp7001DCCConfigurationTable.description: The GDC DCC Configuration table. These are Diagnostic Channel configuration options.

mp7001DCCConfigurationEntry.name: mp7001DCCConfigurationEntry
mp7001DCCConfigurationEntry.description: The GDC Diagnostic Configuration table entry.

mp7001DCCConfigurationIndex.name: mp7001DCCConfigurationIndex
mp7001DCCConfigurationIndex.description: Integer value which uniquely identifies the MP7001 to which this entry is applicable. SCinstance is defined to be ssllddcc where: ss (byte value) - physical shelf slot location (01-32) ll (byte value) - line number (01-128) dd (byte value) - drop number (00-31) cc (byte value) - channel or interface number (always 00)

mp7001Bandwidth.name: mp7001Bandwidth
mp7001Bandwidth.description: Bandwidth to use: 8 kbps - bit 7 only 56 kbps - bits 0 - 6 64 kbps - all 8 bits

mp7001HighwayAssignEntry.name: mp7001HighwayAssignEntry
mp7001HighwayAssignEntry.description: The GDC T1 Highway Assign table entry.

mp7001HighwayAssignIndex.name: mp7001HighwayAssignIndex
mp7001HighwayAssignIndex.description: Integer value which uniquely identifies the MP7001 to which this entry is applicable. SCinstance is defined to be ssllddcc where: ss (byte value) - physical shelf slot location (01-32) ll (byte value) - line number (01-128) dd (byte value) - drop number (00-31) cc (byte value) - channel or interface number (always 00)

mp7001StartTimeSlot.name: mp7001StartTimeSlot
mp7001StartTimeSlot.description: Starting time slot of the bundle. If only 1 bundle is being assigned, or the first of 2 is being assigned, it must start at 1. The second of 2 must start at the next available time slot after the first bundle.

mp7001NumberOfTimeSlots.name: mp7001NumberOfTimeSlots
mp7001NumberOfTimeSlots.description: Number of time slots assigned to the bundle.

mp7001BundleDestination.name: mp7001BundleDestination
mp7001BundleDestination.description: Defines the destination of the bundle.

mp7001ExecuteAssign.name: mp7001ExecuteAssign
mp7001ExecuteAssign.description: Causes the MP7001 to execute configuration of the assigned highway configuration. This object should be sent in a separate PDU after acknowlegement of the assign PDU(s) has been received.

mp7001DiagTable.name: mp7001DiagTable
mp7001DiagTable.description: The GDC T1 Diagnostics table. Information in the entries of this table support diagnostics testing, both active testing via patterns, and passive testing via loopbacks.

mp7001DiagEntry.name: mp7001DiagEntry
mp7001DiagEntry.description: The GDC T1 Diagnostics table entry.

mp7001DiagIndex.name: mp7001DiagIndex
mp7001DiagIndex.description: Integer value which uniquely identifies the MP7001 to which this entry is applicable. SCinstance is defined to be ssllddcc where: ss (byte value) - physical shelf slot location (01-32) ll (byte value) - line number (01-128) dd (byte value) - drop number (00-31) cc (byte value) - channel or interface number (always 00)

mp7001TestPattern.name: mp7001TestPattern
mp7001TestPattern.description: Test pattern for tests that use the pattern generator.

mp7001DiagConfig.name: mp7001DiagConfig
mp7001DiagConfig.description: Selects the test to run. noLoop(1) ends the test.

mp7001TestLimit.name: mp7001TestLimit
mp7001TestLimit.description: Selects the duration to run a diagnostic test. The value(1) noLimit signifies that the test should run indefinitely until explicitly terminated.

mp7001TestExecutionStatus.name: mp7001TestExecutionStatus
mp7001TestExecutionStatus.description: This variable reports the status of a test. notInTest(1) indicates a test is not running. testInProgress(2) indicates that a test is currently running. testCompleted(4) indicates that a test has run and is completed. testCompletedNotInTest(5) indicates that a test has completed and it is no longer in test.

mp7001TestExceptions.name: mp7001TestExceptions
mp7001TestExceptions.description: Indicates exceptions that have occurred that may affect interpretation of the test results. The value of this object is a sum. This sum initially take the value zero. Then, for each exception, the value associated with the exception is added to the sum. The exception values are: value exception 1 a timed test was preempted so the result cannot be viewed in relation to the test duration 2 the results overflowed so the result cannot be viewed as an absolute value 4 the test was performed while synchronization could not be performed so the result may not be accurate.

mp7001TestResults.name: mp7001TestResults
mp7001TestResults.description: The results of the last diagnostic test. This can be the current test running or the last completed test. Note that the interpretation of these results may be affected by the value of the mp7001TestExceptions object.

mp7001DS0Diag.name: mp7001DS0Diag
mp7001DS0Diag.description: Defines a DS0 level diagnostic. Setting this object value to 0 disables a DS0 level diagnostic. Setting this object to a value from 1 to 32 enables a DS0 level diagnostic on the DS0 indicated. Enabling a DS0 level diagnostic bysetting this object to a value from 1 to 32 alters the meaning of the diagnostic test to be specific to the DS0 specified instead of the whole DS1. Note that a DS0 level diagnostic and a DS1 level diagnostic cannot be performed simultaneously.

mp7001NearEndAlarmConfigTable.name: mp7001NearEndAlarmConfigTable
mp7001NearEndAlarmConfigTable.description: This table contains entries that configure Near End Alarm reporting.

mp7001NearEndAlarmConfigEntry.name: mp7001NearEndAlarmConfigEntry
mp7001NearEndAlarmConfigEntry.description: An entry in the MP7001 Alarm Configuration table.

mp7001NearEndAlarmConfigIndex.name: mp7001NearEndAlarmConfigIndex
mp7001NearEndAlarmConfigIndex.description: Integer value which uniquely identifies the MP7001 to which this entry is applicable. SCinstance is defined to be ssllddcc where: ss (byte value) - physical shelf slot location (01-32) ll (byte value) - line number (01-128) dd (byte value) - drop number (00-31) cc (byte value) - channel or interface number (always 00)

mp7001NearEndAlarmConfigIdentifier.name: mp7001NearEndAlarmConfigIdentifier
mp7001NearEndAlarmConfigIdentifier.description: The unique alarm identifier assigned to this alarm type. The format of this identifier is an OBJECT IDENTIFIER that has the following format: {iso(1) org(3) dod(6) internet(1) private(4) enterprises(1) gdc(498) xxx(x) alarm(z) yyy(y) where xxx(x) is the administratively assigned family object identifier (z) is the object identifier for alarms in the family defined MIB and yyy(y) is the administratively assigned alarm type identifier for this alarm.

mp7001NearEndAlarmCountWindow.name: mp7001NearEndAlarmCountWindow
mp7001NearEndAlarmCountWindow.description: This variable sets/reads the alarm window. This window is used with the alarm threshold to determine how long the alarm should be active before reporting. Default: disabled(1)

mp7001NearEndAlarmCountThreshold.name: mp7001NearEndAlarmCountThreshold
mp7001NearEndAlarmCountThreshold.description: This function sets/reads the alarm threshold criteria. This threshold is used along with the the alarm window to determine the number of instances in a given time frame for an alarm to occur before the alarm is considered active. Default: thresGT1(1)

mp7001LocalAlarmConfigTable.name: mp7001LocalAlarmConfigTable
mp7001LocalAlarmConfigTable.description: The mp7001LocalAlarmConfigTable contains entries that configure alarm reporting to the alarm card.

mp7001LocalAlarmConfigEntry.name: mp7001LocalAlarmConfigEntry
mp7001LocalAlarmConfigEntry.description: An entry in the GDC Local Alarm Configuration table.

mp7001LocalAlarmConfigIndex.name: mp7001LocalAlarmConfigIndex
mp7001LocalAlarmConfigIndex.description: Integer value which uniquely identifies the MP7001 to which this entry is applicable. SCinstance is defined to be ssllddcc where: ss (byte value) - physical shelf slot location (01-32) ll (byte value) - line number (01-128) dd (byte value) - drop number (00-31) cc (byte value) - channel or interface number (always 00)

mp7001LOSLocal.name: mp7001LOSLocal
mp7001LOSLocal.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

mp7001LOFLocal.name: mp7001LOFLocal
mp7001LOFLocal.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

mp7001AISLocal.name: mp7001AISLocal
mp7001AISLocal.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

mp7001RxYELLOWLocal.name: mp7001RxYELLOWLocal
mp7001RxYELLOWLocal.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

mp7001BPVLocal.name: mp7001BPVLocal
mp7001BPVLocal.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

mp7001CRCLocal.name: mp7001CRCLocal
mp7001CRCLocal.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

mp7001UnSigStateLocal.name: mp7001UnSigStateLocal
mp7001UnSigStateLocal.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

mp7001TiminglossLocal.name: mp7001TiminglossLocal
mp7001TiminglossLocal.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

mp7001ESLocal.name: mp7001ESLocal
mp7001ESLocal.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

mp7001BESLocal.name: mp7001BESLocal
mp7001BESLocal.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

mp7001SESLocal.name: mp7001SESLocal
mp7001SESLocal.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

mp7001UASLocal.name: mp7001UASLocal
mp7001UASLocal.description: Disables or enables the alarm on the Major buss or Minor buss.

mp7001InboundANSIperfTable.name: mp7001InboundANSIperfTable
mp7001InboundANSIperfTable.description: The GDC ANSI Performance table. Information in the entries of this table support the ANSI Scheduled Performance Reports. Entries supply information for inbound reports for the last 4 seconds.

mp7001InboundANSIperfEntry.name: mp7001InboundANSIperfEntry
mp7001InboundANSIperfEntry.description: The GDC ANSI Performance table entry. The information in this entry presents one of the 4 second periods performance data in the inbound direction.

mp7001InboundANSIperfIndex.name: mp7001InboundANSIperfIndex
mp7001InboundANSIperfIndex.description: Integer value which uniquely identifies the MP7001 to which this entry is applicable. SCinstance is defined to be ssllddcc where: ss (byte value) - physical shelf slot location (01-32) ll (byte value) - line number (01-128) dd (byte value) - drop number (00-31) cc (byte value) - channel or interface number (always 00)

mp7001InboundANSIseconds.name: mp7001InboundANSIseconds
mp7001InboundANSIseconds.description: Identifies the reporting interval. This has the value 1 to 4 supporting up to the last 4 seconds of performance data.

mp7001InboundANSICRCerrorEvents.name: mp7001InboundANSICRCerrorEvents
mp7001InboundANSICRCerrorEvents.description: Identifies the magnitude of the error events in the interval which this entry represents.

mp7001InboundANSIsevereErrors.name: mp7001InboundANSIsevereErrors
mp7001InboundANSIsevereErrors.description: Identifies whether or not any severe errors were detected in the interval which this entry represents.

mp7001InboundANSIframeErrors.name: mp7001InboundANSIframeErrors
mp7001InboundANSIframeErrors.description: Identifies whether or not any framing errors were detected in the interval which this entry represents.

mp7001InboundANSIcodeViolations.name: mp7001InboundANSIcodeViolations
mp7001InboundANSIcodeViolations.description: Identifies whether or not any code violations were detected in the interval which this entry represents.

mp7001InboundANSIcontrolledSlips.name: mp7001InboundANSIcontrolledSlips
mp7001InboundANSIcontrolledSlips.description: Identifies whether or not any controlled slips were detected in the interval which this entry represents.

mp7001InboundANSIactivePayloadLoops.name: mp7001InboundANSIactivePayloadLoops
mp7001InboundANSIactivePayloadLoops.description: Identifies whether or not any active payload loops were detected in the interval which this entry represents.

mp7001OutboundANSIperfTable.name: mp7001OutboundANSIperfTable
mp7001OutboundANSIperfTable.description: The GDC ANSI Performance table. Information in the entries of this table support the ANSI Scheduled Performance Reports. Entries supply information for outbound reports for the last 4 seconds.

mp7001OutboundANSIperfEntry.name: mp7001OutboundANSIperfEntry
mp7001OutboundANSIperfEntry.description: The GDC ANSI Performance table entry. The information in this entry presents one of the 4 second periods performance data in the outbound direction.

mp7001OutboundANSIseconds.name: mp7001OutboundANSIseconds
mp7001OutboundANSIseconds.description: Identifies the reporting interval. This has the value 1 to 4 supporting up to the last 4 seconds of performance data.

mp7001OutboundANSICRCerrorEvents.name: mp7001OutboundANSICRCerrorEvents

mp7001OutboundANSIframeErrors.name: mp7001OutboundANSIframeErrors
mp7001OutboundANSIframeErrors.description: Identifies whether or not any framing errors were detected in the interval which this entry represents.

mp7001OutboundANSIcodeViolations.name: mp7001OutboundANSIcodeViolations
mp7001OutboundANSIcodeViolations.description: Identifies whether or not any code violations were detected in the interval which this entry represents.

mp7001OutboundANSIcontrolledSlips.name: mp7001OutboundANSIcontrolledSlips
mp7001OutboundANSIcontrolledSlips.description: Identifies whether or not any controlled slips were detected in the interval which this entry represents.

mp7001OutboundANSIactivePayloadLoops.name: mp7001OutboundANSIactivePayloadLoops
mp7001OutboundANSIactivePayloadLoops.description: Identifies whether or not any active payload loops were detected in the interval which this entry represents.

mp7001IntervalEntry.description: An entry in the DS1 Interval table.

mp7001IntervalIndex.description: Integer value which uniquely identifies the MP7001 to which this entry is applicable. SCinstance is defined to be ssllddcc where: ss (byte value) - physical shelf slot location (01-32) ll (byte value) - line number (01-128) dd (byte value) - drop number (00-31) cc (byte value) - channel or interface number (always 00)

mp7001IntervalNumber.name: mp7001IntervalNumber
mp7001IntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minutes interval (assuming that all 96 intervals are valid).
